#. <section class="sutta" id="mn103"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn103:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 103"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 103"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn103:0.2"
msgid "Kintisutta"
msgstr "Is This What You Think Of Me?"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. VAR: pisinārāyaṃ → kusinārāyaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn103:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā pisinārāyaṃ viharati baliharaṇe vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Kusināra, in the Forest of Offerings."

msgctxt "mn103:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn103:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn103:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn103:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:2.1"
msgid "“kinti vo, bhikkhave, mayi hoti:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, is this what you think of me?"

msgctxt "mn103:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘cīvarahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, piṇḍapātahetu vā samaṇo gotamo "
"dhammaṃ deseti, senāsanahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, "
"itibhavābhavahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama teaches the Dhamma for the sake of robes, alms-food, "
"lodgings, or rebirth in this or that state.’”"

msgctxt "mn103:2.3"
msgid "“Na kho no, bhante, bhagavati evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“No sir, we don’t think of you that way.”"

msgctxt "mn103:2.4"
msgid ""
"‘cīvarahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, piṇḍapātahetu vā samaṇo gotamo "
"dhammaṃ deseti, senāsanahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, "
"itibhavābhavahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:2.5"
msgid "“Na ca kira vo, bhikkhave, mayi evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“If you don’t think of me that way,"

msgctxt "mn103:2.6"
msgid "‘cīvarahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn103:2.7"
msgid "itibhavābhavahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’ti;"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: atha kinti carahi vo → atha kinti vo (pts1) | atha kiñcarahi vo (mr)
msgctxt "mn103:2.8"
msgid "atha kinti carahi vo, bhikkhave, mayi hotī”ti?"
msgstr "then what exactly do you think of me?”"

msgctxt "mn103:2.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavati hoti:"
msgstr "“We think of you this way:"

msgctxt "mn103:2.10"
msgid "‘anukampako bhagavā hitesī;"
msgstr "‘The Buddha is compassionate and wants what’s best for us."

msgctxt "mn103:2.11"
msgid "anukampaṃ upādāya dhammaṃ desetī’”ti."
msgstr "He teaches out of compassion.’”"

msgctxt "mn103:2.12"
msgid "“Evañca kira vo, bhikkhave, mayi hoti:"
msgstr "“If you think of me that way,"

msgctxt "mn103:2.13"
msgid "‘anukampako bhagavā hitesī;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn103:2.14"
msgid "anukampaṃ upādāya dhammaṃ desetī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.239"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: vo → ye te (mr)
msgctxt "mn103:3.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ye vo mayā dhammā abhiññā desitā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"then each and every one of you should train in the things I have taught from "
"my direct knowledge, that is,"

msgctxt "mn103:3.2"
msgid ""
"cattāro satipaṭṭhānā cattāro sammappadhānā cattāro iddhipādā pañcindriyāni "
"pañca balāni satta bojjhaṅgā ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, tattha sabbeheva "
"samaggehi sammodamānehi avivadamānehi sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right efforts, the four "
"bases of psychic power, the five faculties, the five powers, the seven "
"awakening factors, and the noble eightfold path. You should train in these "
"things in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. VAR: siyaṃsu → tattha siyuṃ (bj) | siyā (s1) | siyuṃ (s2, s3, km)
msgctxt "mn103:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tesañca vo, bhikkhave, samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ "
"siyaṃsu dve bhikkhū abhidhamme nānāvādā."
msgstr ""
"As you do so, it may happen that two mendicants disagree about the teaching."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:5.1"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa:"
msgstr "Now, you might think:"

#. VAR: suvacataraṃ → subbacataraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn103:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘imesaṃ kho āyasmantānaṃ atthato ceva nānaṃ byañjanato ca nānan’ti, tattha "
"yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"‘These two venerables disagree on both the meaning and the phrasing.’ So you "
"should approach whichever mendicant you think is most amenable and say to "
"them:"

msgctxt "mn103:5.3"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ."
msgstr "‘The venerables disagree on the meaning and the phrasing."

#. VAR: Tadamināpetaṃ → tadimināpetaṃ (s2, s3, km)
msgctxt "mn103:5.4"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:5.5"
msgid "yathā atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ."
msgstr "such disagreement on the meaning and the phrasing comes to be."

msgctxt "mn103:5.6"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’"

msgctxt "mn103:5.7"
msgid ""
"Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha "
"so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Then they should approach whichever mendicant they think is most amenable "
"among those who side with the other party and say to them:"

msgctxt "mn103:5.8"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ."
msgstr "‘The venerables disagree on the meaning and the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:5.9"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:5.10"
msgid "yathā atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ."
msgstr "such disagreement on the meaning and the phrasing comes to be."

msgctxt "mn103:5.11"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’"

msgctxt "mn103:5.12"
msgid ""
"Iti duggahitaṃ duggahitato dhāretabbaṃ, suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"So you should remember what has been incorrectly memorized as incorrectly "
"memorized and what has been correctly memorized as correctly memorized."

msgctxt "mn103:5.13"
msgid ""
"Duggahitaṃ duggahitato dhāretvā suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretvā yo dhammo yo "
"vinayo so bhāsitabbo."
msgstr "Remembering this, you should speak on the teaching and the training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.240"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:6.1"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa:"
msgstr "Now, you might think:"

msgctxt "mn103:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘imesaṃ kho āyasmantānaṃ atthato hi kho nānaṃ, byañjanato sametī’ti, tattha "
"yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"‘These two venerables disagree on the meaning but agree on the phrasing.’ So "
"you should approach whichever mendicant you think is most amenable and say "
"to them:"

msgctxt "mn103:6.3"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato hi nānaṃ, byañjanato sameti."
msgstr "‘The venerables disagree on the meaning but agree on the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:6.4"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:6.5"
msgid "yathā atthato hi kho nānaṃ, byañjanato sameti."
msgstr ""
"such disagreement on the meaning and agreement on the phrasing comes to be."

msgctxt "mn103:6.6"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’"

msgctxt "mn103:6.7"
msgid ""
"Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha "
"so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Then they should approach whichever mendicant they think is most amenable "
"among those who side with the other party and say to them:"

msgctxt "mn103:6.8"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato hi kho nānaṃ, byañjanato sameti."
msgstr "‘The venerables disagree on the meaning but agree on the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:6.9"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:6.10"
msgid "yathā atthato hi kho nānaṃ, byañjanato sameti."
msgstr ""
"such disagreement on the meaning and agreement on the phrasing comes to be."

msgctxt "mn103:6.11"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’"

msgctxt "mn103:6.12"
msgid ""
"Iti duggahitaṃ duggahitato dhāretabbaṃ, suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"So you should remember what has been incorrectly memorized as incorrectly "
"memorized and what has been correctly memorized as correctly memorized."

msgctxt "mn103:6.13"
msgid ""
"Duggahitaṃ duggahitato dhāretvā suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretvā yo dhammo yo "
"vinayo so bhāsitabbo."
msgstr "Remembering this, you should speak on the teaching and the training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:7.1"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa:"
msgstr "Now, you might think:"

msgctxt "mn103:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘imesaṃ kho āyasmantānaṃ atthato hi kho sameti, byañjanato nānan’ti, tattha "
"yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"‘These two venerables agree on the meaning but disagree on the phrasing.’ So "
"you should approach whichever mendicant you think is most amenable and say "
"to them:"

msgctxt "mn103:7.3"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato hi sameti, byañjanato nānaṃ."
msgstr "‘The venerables agree on the meaning but disagree on the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:7.4"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:7.5"
msgid "yathā atthato hi kho sameti, byañjanato nānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"such agreement on the meaning and disagreement on the phrasing comes to be."

msgctxt "mn103:7.6"
msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—byañjanaṃ."
msgstr "But the phrasing is a minor matter."

msgctxt "mn103:7.7"
msgid "Māyasmanto appamattake vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about something so minor.’"

msgctxt "mn103:7.8"
msgid ""
"Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha "
"so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Then they should approach whichever mendicant they think is most amenable "
"among those who side with the other party and say to them:"

msgctxt "mn103:7.9"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato hi sameti, byañjanato nānaṃ."
msgstr "‘The venerables agree on the meaning but disagree on the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:7.10"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:7.11"
msgid "yathā atthato hi kho sameti, byañjanato nānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"such agreement on the meaning and disagreement on the phrasing comes to be."

msgctxt "mn103:7.12"
msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—byañjanaṃ."
msgstr "But the phrasing is a minor matter."

msgctxt "mn103:7.13"
msgid "Māyasmanto appamattake vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about something so minor.’"

