"vinayo so bhāsitabbo."
msgstr "Remembering this, you should speak on the teaching and the training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.241"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:8.1"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa:"
msgstr "Now, you might think:"

msgctxt "mn103:8.2"
msgid ""
"‘imesaṃ kho āyasmantānaṃ atthato ceva sameti byañjanato ca sametī’ti, tattha "
"yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"‘These two venerables agree on both the meaning and the phrasing.’ So you "
"should approach whichever mendicant you think is most amenable and say to "
"them:"

msgctxt "mn103:8.3"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato ceva sameti, byañjanato ca sameti."
msgstr "‘The venerables agree on both the meaning and the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:8.4"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:8.5"
msgid "yathā atthato ceva sameti byañjanato ca sameti."
msgstr "they come to agree on the meaning and the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:8.6"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’"

msgctxt "mn103:8.7"
msgid ""
"Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha "
"so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Then they should approach whichever mendicant they think is most amenable "
"among those who side with the other party and say to them:"

msgctxt "mn103:8.8"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato ceva sameti byañjanato ca sameti."
msgstr "‘The venerables agree on both the meaning and the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:8.9"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how"

msgctxt "mn103:8.10"
msgid "yathā atthato ceva sameti byañjanato ca sameti."
msgstr "they come to agree on the meaning and the phrasing."

msgctxt "mn103:8.11"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’"

msgctxt "mn103:8.12"
msgid "Iti suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"So you should remember what has been correctly memorized as correctly "
"memorized."

msgctxt "mn103:8.13"
msgid "Suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretvā yo dhammo yo vinayo so bhāsitabbo."
msgstr "Remembering this, you should speak on the teaching and the training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: taritabbaṃ → coditabbaṃ (s1-3, km, mr) | turitabbaṃ (?)
msgctxt "mn103:9.1"
msgid ""
"Tesañca vo, bhikkhave, samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ "
"siyā aññatarassa bhikkhuno āpatti siyā vītikkamo,"
msgstr ""
"As you train in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, one of "
"the mendicants might commit an offense or transgression. "

# Punctuation in MS is incorrect: the following iti belongs on this line, as shown in the repetition below.
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:10.1"
msgid "tatra, bhikkhave, na codanāya taritabbaṃ. Puggalo upaparikkhitabbo:"
msgstr ""
"In such a case, you should not be in a hurry to accuse them. The individual "
"should be examined like this:"

msgctxt "mn103:10.2"
msgid ""
"‘iti mayhañca avihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa anupaghāto, paro hi "
"puggalo akkodhano anupanāhī adaḷhadiṭṭhī suppaṭinissaggī, sakkomi cāhaṃ etaṃ "
"puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I won’t be troubled and the other individual won’t be hurt, for they’re not "
"angry and hostile. They don’t hold fast to their views, but let them go "
"easily. I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the "
"skillful.’"

msgctxt "mn103:10.3"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya."
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:11.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, evamassa:"
msgstr "But if you think this:"

msgctxt "mn103:11.2"
msgid ""
"‘mayhaṃ kho avihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa upaghāto, paro hi "
"puggalo kodhano upanāhī adaḷhadiṭṭhī suppaṭinissaggī, sakkomi cāhaṃ etaṃ "
"puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘I will be troubled and the other individual will be hurt, for they’re angry "
"and hostile. However, they don’t hold fast to their views, but let them go "
"easily. I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the "
"skillful."

msgctxt "mn103:11.3"
msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—parassa puggalassa upaghāto."
msgstr "But for the other individual to get hurt is a minor matter."

msgctxt "mn103:11.4"
msgid "Atha kho etadeva bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "It’s more important"

msgctxt "mn103:11.5"
msgid ""
"svāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti."
msgstr ""
"that I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the "
"skillful.’"

msgctxt "mn103:11.6"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya."
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:12.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, evamassa:"
msgstr "But if you think this:"

msgctxt "mn103:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘mayhaṃ kho vihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa anupaghāto. Paro hi "
"puggalo akkodhano anupanāhī daḷhadiṭṭhī duppaṭinissaggī, sakkomi cāhaṃ etaṃ "
"puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘I will be troubled but the other individual won’t be hurt, for they’re not "
"angry and hostile. However, they hold fast to their views, refusing to let "
"go. Nevertheless, I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish "
"them in the skillful."

msgctxt "mn103:12.3"
msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—mayhaṃ vihesā."
msgstr "But for me to be troubled is a minor matter."

msgctxt "mn103:12.4"
msgid "Atha kho etadeva bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "It’s more important"

msgctxt "mn103:12.5"
msgid ""
"svāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti."
msgstr ""
"that I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the "
"skillful.’"

msgctxt "mn103:12.6"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya."
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.242"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:13.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, evamassa:"
msgstr "But if you think this:"

msgctxt "mn103:13.2"
msgid ""
"‘mayhañca kho vihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa upaghāto. Paro hi "
"puggalo kodhano upanāhī daḷhadiṭṭhī duppaṭinissaggī, sakkomi cāhaṃ etaṃ "
"puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘I will be troubled and the other individual will be hurt, for they’re angry "
"and hostile. And they hold fast to their views, refusing to let go. "
"Nevertheless, I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in "
"the skillful."

msgctxt "mn103:13.3"
msgid ""
"Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—mayhañca vihesā bhavissati parassa ca "
"puggalassa upaghāto."
msgstr ""
"But for me to be troubled and the other individual to get hurt is a minor "
"matter."

msgctxt "mn103:13.4"
msgid "Atha kho etadeva bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "It’s more important"

msgctxt "mn103:13.5"
msgid ""
"svāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti."
msgstr ""
"that I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the "
"skillful.’"

msgctxt "mn103:13.6"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya."
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:14.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, evamassa:"
msgstr "But if you think this:"

msgctxt "mn103:14.2"
msgid ""
"‘mayhañca kho vihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa upaghāto. Paro hi "
"puggalo kodhano upanāhī daḷhadiṭṭhī duppaṭinissaggī, na cāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ "
"puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I will be troubled and the other individual will be hurt, for they’re angry "
"and hostile. And they hold fast to their views, refusing to let go. I cannot "
"draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful.’"

msgctxt "mn103:14.3"
msgid "Evarūpe, bhikkhave, puggale upekkhā nātimaññitabbā."
msgstr "Don’t underestimate the value of equanimity for such a person."

# Var readings vacisamhara, vacisamsara, vacisankhara: Comm: Vacīsaṃhāroti vacanasañcāro. Imehi kathitaṃ amūsaṃ antaraṃ paveseyya, tumhe imehi idañcidañca vuttāti amūhi kathitaṃ imesaṃ antaraṃ paveseyyāti attho, Tika: Vacanasañcāroti pesuññavasena aññathāvacanupasaṃhāro. The parallel passage is at AN 2.63, where samsara is the MS reading, and adopted by BB there. Comm there gives a completely different explanation: ubhato vacīsaṃsāroti dvīsupi pakkhesu aññamaññaṃ akkosanapaccakkosanavasena saṃsaramānā vācā vacīsaṃsāro. Tika has: Saṃsaramānāti pavattamānā. Despite this, I think the reading samhara makes better sense, as per MN comm.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
#. VAR: diṭṭhipaḷāso → diṭṭhipalāso (bj, mr)
#. VAR: vacīsaṃhāro → vacīsaṃsāro (bj) | vacīsaṅkhāro (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn103:15.1"
msgid ""
"Tesañca vo, bhikkhave, samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ "
"aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppajjeyya diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo "
"anabhiraddhi."
msgstr ""
"As you train in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, mutual "
"tale-bearing might come up, with contempt for each other’s views, resentful, "
"bitter, and exasperated."

msgctxt "mn103:15.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so "
"upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"In this case you should approach whichever mendicant you think is most "
"amenable among those who side with one party and say to them:"

#. VAR: samaṇo → samāno (bj, mr)
msgctxt "mn103:15.3"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ "
"aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo "
"anabhiraddhi, taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, as we were training, mutual tale-bearing came up. If the Ascetic "
"knew about this, would he rebuke it?’"

msgctxt "mn103:15.4"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say:"

msgctxt "mn103:15.5"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ "
"aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo "
"anabhiraddhi, taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyāti."
msgstr "‘Yes, reverend, he would.’"

msgctxt "mn103:15.6"
msgid "Etaṃ panāvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti."
msgstr "‘But without giving that up, reverend, can one realize extinguishment?’"

msgctxt "mn103:15.7"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say:"

msgctxt "mn103:15.8"
msgid "‘etaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya na nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti."
msgstr "‘No, reverend, one cannot.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.243"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:16.1"
msgid ""
"Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ "
"maññeyyātha, so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Then they should approach whichever mendicant they think is most amenable "
"among those who side with the other party and say to them:"

msgctxt "mn103:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ "
"aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo "
"anabhiraddhi, taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, as we were training, mutual tale-bearing came up. If the Ascetic "
"knew about this, would he rebuke it?’"

msgctxt "mn103:16.3"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say:"

msgctxt "mn103:16.4"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ "
"aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo "
"anabhiraddhi taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyāti."
msgstr "‘Yes, reverend, he would.’"

msgctxt "mn103:16.5"
msgid "Etaṃ panāvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti."
msgstr "‘But without giving that up, reverend, can one realize extinguishment?’"

msgctxt "mn103:16.6"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say:"

msgctxt "mn103:16.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ kho, āvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya na nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti."
msgstr "‘No, reverend, one cannot.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:17.1"
msgid "Tañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ pare evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "If others should ask that mendicant:"

msgctxt "mn103:17.2"
msgid "‘āyasmatā no ete bhikkhū akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpitā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Were you the venerable who drew those mendicants away from the unskillful "
"and established them in the skillful?’"

msgctxt "mn103:17.3"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say:"

msgctxt "mn103:17.4"
msgid ""
"‘idhāhaṃ, āvuso, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃ, tassa me bhagavā dhammaṃ "
"desesi, tāhaṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Well, reverends, I approached the Buddha. He taught me the Dhamma. After "
"hearing that teaching I explained it to those mendicants."

msgctxt "mn103:17.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ te bhikkhū dhammaṃ sutvā akusalā vuṭṭhahiṃsu, kusale patiṭṭhahiṃsū’ti."
msgstr ""
"When those mendicants heard that teaching they were drawn away from the "
"unskillful and established in the skillful.’"

msgctxt "mn103:17.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na ceva attānaṃ ukkaṃseti, na paraṃ "
"vambheti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaroti, na ca koci sahadhammiko "
"vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Answering in this way, that mendicant doesn’t glorify themselves or put "
"others down. They answer in line with the teaching, with no legitimate "
"grounds for rebuke and criticism.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn103:17.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn103:17.8"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn103:17.9"
msgid "Kintisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
